    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="213"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/905</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Peruvian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prada</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the Chargé d’Affaires ad
                    interim of Peru, and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of his note of
                    April 30, 1922,<note n="6" xml:id="d213fn6">Not printed.</note> to the effect
                    that the delegates who will represent the Government of Peru at the Conference
                    to be held with the delegates of the Chilean Government, are to arrive in this
                    city in the near future, and that no objection is perceived on the part of the
                    Peruvian delegation to opening this Conference on the 12th of May next.</p>
                <p>This information will be transmitted to the Chilean Embassy in Washington, with a
                    view to fixing May 12th as the date for the opening of the Conference.<note
                        n="7" xml:id="d213fn7">This date was accepted by the Chilean Ambassador, but
                        was later changed to May 15 by agreement between the Chilean and Peruvian
                        Ambassadors.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1922</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
